cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use or build on this artifact, please cite it."
title: "Compitum: A Lyapunov-Stable Bounded Observer for Verifiable Routing"
authors:
  - family-names: Tiffany
    given-names: Paul C.
    affiliation: Independent Researcher
date-released: 2026-06-07
license: MIT
url: "https://compitum.space"
repository-code: "https://github.com/PaulTiffany/compitum"
abstract: >-
  A self-published artifact describing Compitum, a geometrically-aware LLM router that
  selects a model by minimizing a scalarized Symbolic Free Energy over a learned SPD metric
  under feasibility-first constraints, with a Lyapunov-style controller gating two-timescale
  online updates. Its contribution is verifiability by construction: structural and dynamical
  properties are stated as assumptions, derived as lemmas, and pinned to runnable property-based
  tests, with an honest empirical reading that includes a negative result. Incomplete by construction.
keywords:
  - LLM routing
  - Lyapunov stability
  - SPD metric learning
  - bounded observer
  - anti-masking
  - falsifiable evaluation
